commit.message:
Make Pandoc a hard requirement

- Pandoc has been made a hard requirement so the package can no longer
  be accidentally uploaded to PyPI without a description.

Bump version to 0.1.3

- The version has been bumped to 0.1.2 because I apparently uploaded a
  release marked with that version in the past.

Add handler for offset increments

- This change adds handling of simplified offset increments. Offset
  increments are where you want a cron job to run every "N" periods, but
  not starting at period 0. For instance, if you wanted a job to start
  every 15 minutes, at xx:05, xx:20, xx:35, and xx:50, the cron
  expression would look like "5/15 * * * *". Although Cronex already
  supported this via the more verbose "5-59/15 * * * *" notation, this
  change allows that to be simplified and aligns with the Quartz
  Scheduler implementation of cron.

Fixed unit test for repeaters in the months field

- In https://github.com/ericpruitt/cronex/issues/6, Matthew Hall
  reported that test_periodics_month was failing. The unit test was
  written with the incorrect assumption that 1,337 days would always
  span 44 calendar months. The unit test has been rewritten so that
  assumption has been abandoned, and the test no longer depends on the
  host's clock.

Accept Unicode strings in Python 2

- The function str.upper has been removed so creating a CronExpression
  with a Unicode string in Python 2 will not raise an exception. Since
  the code expects the atoms "L" and "W" to be capitalized, month and
  day-of-the-week replacement now normalize strings using the "upper"
  method instead of "lower," and the strings in the name mappings have
  been updated accordingly.
Support for both distutils and setuptools
Support for easily publishing wheels
Fixed typo in README

Prepared setup.py for PyPI upload

- The setup.py file has been modified to include classifier information,
  and if Pandoc is available, it will convert the README to REstructured
  Text so that it can be shown on the PyPI page.

Python 2.4 compatiblity

- Discovered the CronExpression code was only a few lines away from
  Python 2.4 copatibility and tweaked it accordingly.

Updated documentation

- Added a longer synopsis to the documentation.
- Fixed a formatting issue, renamed a header and added some more context
  to each of the examples.
Added explanation to CHANGELOG.deprecated

Repository-meta tweaks

- The CHANGELOG has been renamed to CHANGELOG.deprecated since I now
  write reasonable commit messages.
- Removed the copyright year from the LICENSE file.
- Modified the __license__ metadata of the cronex package to list one
  license.
- Renamed README.markdown to README.md.

Code clean-up, improved PEP 8 compliance

- Added docstrings to all unit test functions and some comments to
  explain some of the less obvious parts of the code.
- Minor tweaks here and there to improve PEP 8 compliance.
- Removed a couple of vestigial branches of code.
- Sorted imports in cronex and cronex.tests.
- Swapped out the implementation body of __str__ with __repr__ in the
  CronExpression class.
Moved SYNTAX documentation into README.md

Shuffled project directory structure

- The cronex source code has been moved into a package folder with an
  __init__.py file out of the repository root for a cleaner, less
  cluttered layout.
Removed first name from LICENSE and setup.py
Created setup.py to enable pip installation
Added license file
Removed extraneous subtraction
Fixed bug in test
Revamed documentation
Fix wrap-range bug
Fix for Nov 15 flaw.
Python 3.1 compatibility.
Field length checking
__init__ file for submodule
Syntax validation
Did not realize 'add' made a snapshot then and there.
README change
